# Live Activities – Implementation Walkthrough

## Summary

Added Live Activities (iOS 16.1+) support to the Home Assistant Companion iOS app. Users can now start, update, and end Live Activities on their Lock Screen and Dynamic Island via push notifications sent from Home Assistant automations.

## Files Created

### Data Model & Manager (`Sources/Shared/LiveActivity/`)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [LiveActivityAttributes.swift](file:///c:/Users/gaschler/AntiGravity/iOS/Sources/Shared/LiveActivity/LiveActivityAttributes.swift) | `ActivityAttributes` model with `ContentState` (value, icon, subtitle, color, progress) |
| [LiveActivityManager.swift](file:///c:/Users/gaschler/AntiGravity/iOS/Sources/Shared/LiveActivity/LiveActivityManager.swift) | Singleton manager: start/update/end activities, push token registration via `ios.live_activity_token` event |

